{"files": {"SKILL.md": "# Verifier-first closure\n\nThe verifier \u2014 not your judgment, not your reading of the diff \u2014 decides whether a task is done. Each step has one product. The step is finished only when its product exists. A description of intended work is not a product.\n\n## 1. Read\n\nIn a batched call, read everything the project puts in front of you: the task description, the surrounding instructions, any acceptance criteria, the verification or test files that define pass, and the files the task names. Read parallel independent slices in one round.\n\nIf a verification file exists, read it completely. Each assertion or check is a row of the contract \u2014 your output must satisfy each one. The shape of your output must match what each assertion compares against.\n\nStop reading when you can name three things:\n1. The deliverable \u2014 what artifact you must produce.\n2. The path \u2014 where it must land.\n3. The pass signal \u2014 what observable result the verifier emits when the deliverable is correct.\n\nIf a notes directory at `/workspace/learned/` exists from earlier work, scan it first. Prior corrections about defect categories or recurring failure shapes save more time than they take.\n\n## 2. Contract\n\nWrite the three things from step 1 in one line: deliverable, exact path, observable pass signal. If the verifier is a command or script, write that command. This is the finish line. You cannot aim for a finish line you have not written down.\n\n## 3. Build\n\nWrite the smallest implementation that satisfies the contract. Match the local style by reading one or two nearby files of the same kind. No drive-by refactors, no helpers used only once, no defensive branches the contract does not promise.\n\nHonour implied invariants \u2014 bounds, values at the edge of a range, concurrency safety, cancellation paths, cleanup of anything that accumulates, idempotence on re-run \u2014 whether the task spells them out or not. When a change touches values at an edge, decide explicitly which side is included. When the work involves concurrency, async cancellation, or shared state, ensure the cancellation, cleanup, and idempotence paths exist alongside the happy path. When code consumes external input \u2014 text files, structured records, log streams, raw bytes \u2014 handle the empty case, the duplicate case, the malformed case, and the boundary of any window.\n\nIf your notes record a fix for a similar shape from prior work, apply that fix at the start rather than rediscovering it.\n\n## 4. Verify\n\nRun the verifier named in step 2. Read the output to the end, not the exit signal alone. The verifier is the source of truth \u2014 your reading of the diff, your sense that it \"should work\", and the absence of new errors are all provisional until the verifier agrees.\n\nIf the verifier fails, identify the root cause, not the surface symptom. The same symptom returns until the root cause is fixed. Re-enter step 3 with the diagnosis sharpened \u2014 change the diagnosis, not the punctuation, before a second full patch cycle. If multiple checks exist, run them all; passing one while breaking another is no progress.\n\n## 5. Close\n\nConfirm the deliverable is at the path the contract named, the verifier produces the pass signal the contract named, and any artifacts the task asked for are visible to the next process that reads the working area. If a contract row has no satisfying artifact, the task is not done; return to step 3.\n\n## Persistent notes\n\nIf `/workspace/learned/` exists and is writable, keep it tight:\n\n- `PATTERNS.md` \u2014 short rules that have proven useful on similar work. One line each.\n- `DEFECTS.md` \u2014 categories of defect encountered and the corrected approach. Format: `<category> | <symptom> | <correction>`. One line per category.\n- `INDEX.md` \u2014 top patterns currently in heavy rotation, promoted only after repeated success.\n\nHabits: write the moment a surprise lands; only verified outcomes go in; update in place; replace stale lines when current observation contradicts; skip language-generic knowledge or values reproducible from version control.\n\nWhen a task begins, scan these. If the present task smells like a recurrence \u2014 same defect category, same shape \u2014 start from the recorded correction rather than from scratch.\n\n## Tool budget\n\nBatch independent probes in one round. Serialize writes per surface \u2014 one write, then re-inspect, then the next. Near a deadline, ship the smallest finished slice that satisfies the verifier \u2014 partial proof beats endless intake.\n\n## Exit\n\nSteps complete for the named deliverable, every contract row honoured, the verifier green \u2014 stop. Action ended is progress; another paragraph is not.\n"}, "schema_version": 1}